      "summary": ": Fri-yay!! Bluebird day on the mountain today, and it's an absolute cracker. Not a cloud in sight, with clear skies stretching over the Southern Alps and Lake Wānaka looking postcard-perfect. Temps are sitting mild for the middle of winter on the lower mountain, making for comfortable cruising all day. The upper mountain is a bit breezy making for colder conditions. Base area conditions are firm and fast first thing, softening up nicely as the sun gets to work. On piste, it's all go — the earth moving last night didn't slow down our night crews who were busy while we all slept refreshing the mountain. Grooming is in top shape and carving conditions on Triple Treat are excellent from top to bottom. If you're chasing the good stuff off-piste, keep an eye out on the upper mountain, where recent wind has loaded up some lovely pockets of soft, wind-blown snow tucked into the terrain. Can't wait to see you up here!",
